sbpro-card
    .card-header Font Weight Utilities
    .card-body
        h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Bootstrap Defaults:
        .border.border-lg.rounded.mb-4
            .p-4.border-bottom
                .p-3.border.mb-3.fw-bold Bold text.
                .p-3.border.mb-3.fw-bolder Bolder weight text (relative to the parent element).
                .p-3.border.mb-3.fw-normal Normal weight text.
                .p-3.border.mb-3.fw-light Light weight text.
                .p-3.border.fw-lighter Lighter weight text (relative to the parent element).

            .bg-light.p-4.small
                | By default, Bootstrap has a number of text utilities that you can use to change the font weight.
                
        h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Extended Utilities:
        .border.border-lg.rounded
            .p-4.border-bottom
                .row.gx-4
                    .col-6
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-100 .fw-100
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-200 .fw-200
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-300 .fw-300
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-400 .fw-400
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-0.fw-500 .fw-500
                    .col-6
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-600 .fw-600
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-700 .fw-700
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-3.fw-800 .fw-800
                        h6.p-3.border.mb-0.fw-900 .fw-900
            .bg-light.p-4.small.
                SB Admin Pro has extended font weight utilities to include specific font weights, for use wherever you want to show a specialized font weight. 
                Note that the font weights are only supported if the font that you are using supports the specified font weight.
